e: Frame of positions\nparam position_array: |-\n  Numpy array of positions i.e. \\[[x,y,z],[x,y,z]\\].\n  Needs to be shape (N,3)\n---\n"]}, {"name": "alitra.models.position.Positions.__str__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["---\nreturn: Unique string representation of the position, ignoring the frame\n---\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "alitra.models.position.Positions.positions", "type": {"name": "List", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.List", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Position", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.position.Position", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "alitra.models.position.Positions.frame", "type": {"name": "Frame", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.position.frame.Frame", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Positions contains a list of positions as well as a frame in which the points\nare valid"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "alitra.models", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "alitra.models.Bounds", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.bounds.Bounds", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.Frame", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.frame.Frame", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.Map", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.map.Map", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.MapAlignment", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.map.MapAlignment", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.Orientation", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.orientation.Orientation", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.Pose", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.pose.Pose", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.Position", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.position.Position", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.Positions", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.position.Positions", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.models.Translation", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.translation.Translation", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "alitra", "documentation": ["Alitra makes alignment and transformation between coordinate-frames\neasier by using custom dataclasses\n\nImagine we have an \"asset\" with one coordinate-frame and a \"robot\" with its own\ninternal coordinate-frame. We want to transform a position in the robot coordinate-frame\nto a position in the asset coordinate-frame.\n\n```pycon\n>>> import numpy as np\n>>> from alitra.models import Positions, Transform, Translation\n```\n\nSetting up rotations, translations and positions for transformation\n\n```pycon\n>>> robot_frame = Frame(\"robot\")\n>>> asset_frame = Frame(\"asset\")\n>>> euler = np.array([np.pi / 4, 0, 0])\n>>> translation = Translation(x=1, y=0, from_=robot_frame, to_=asset_frame)\n>>> p_robot = Positions.from_array(np.array([[1, 1, 0], [10, 1, 0]]), frame=robot_frame)\n>>> rotation_axes = \"z\"\n```\n\nMaking the transform\n\n```pycon\n>>> transform = Transform.from_euler_array(\n...    translation=translation, euler=euler, from_=robot_frame, to_=asset_frame\n... )\n```\n\nTranform position on robot to a position on the asset\n\n```pycon\n>>> p_asset = transform.transform_position(p_robot, from_=robot_frame, to_=asset_frame)\n```\n\nIf you have one position in two different frames and the rotation between the axes you can find the transform\nbetween the two frames.\n\n```pycon\n>>> transform = Transform(p_robot, p_asset, rotation_axes)\n```\n"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "alitra.align_maps", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.alignment.align_maps", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.align_positions", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.alignment.align_positions", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.Bounds", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.Bounds", "project": null}}, {"name": "alitra.Frame", "xref": {"fqname": "alitra.models.Frame", "project": null